-- Brazil Approves $7.3 Billion of Loans for BNDES, Estado Says
-- B y   M a r i o   S e r g i o   L i m a
-- 2013-01-01T14:36:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-01-01/brazil-approves-7-3-billion-of-loans-for-bndes-estado-says.html
Brazil ’s government made a 15 billion
reais ($7.3 billion) loan to BNDES, the nation’s public
development bank, O Estado de S. Paulo newspaper reported today.  The loan is the last tranche of 45 billion reais of lending
in 2012 from the government to the public bank, which is
expected to use the money to increase credit for new
investments, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
